-- Cotton Gains to Record, Jumping by Exchange Limit for Third Straight Day
-- B y   J a e   H u r
-- 2010-12-20T02:26:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/cotton-gains-to-record-jumping-by-exchange-limit-for-third-straight-day.html
Cotton futures in New York gained to
a record, jumping by the exchange limit of 4 cents a pound for
the third straight day.  The March-delivery contract advanced by as much as 2.7
percent to an all-time high of $1.5412 a pound before trading at
$1.5391 at 10:25 a.m. in Singapore.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jae Hur in Singapore at 
